 Port Elizabeth - Some welcome rain fell overnight, but unfortunately this was confined to the coastal belt between Plettenberg Bay and Port Alfred, the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service said on Thursday. "Port Elizabet recorded 1,0 mm at the airport and 10 mm at Riverstone Bridge," described Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape Region. "Plettenberg Bay and Port Alfred, as well as the Catchment at Kareedouw, only received around one and a half mm." Station Names 31 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 1.0 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 5.8 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 4.2 ARS Chatty 7.6 AWS Coega 3.0 AWSH Fettes Road 3.2 ARS Flower Reserve 3.6 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 9.8 ARS St Albans 3.0 AWS Uitenhage * Man Woodridge 3.1 Catchment  AWS Joubertina NIL ARS Kareedouw 1.4 Man Kareedouw NIL Man Kouga Dam NIL AWS Patensie NIL    Other Towns  AWS Addo NIL AWS Bisho/KWT NIL AWS Cape St Francis 3.8 AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London NIL AWS Fort Beaufort NIL AWS George NIL AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown NIL AWS Henry`s Flats NIL AWS Joubertina NIL AWS Mossel Bay NIL AWS Mthatha NIL AWS Plettenberg bay 1.4 AWS Port Alfred 1.6 AWS Queenstown NIL  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.    